Pause the status spinner while a tall extension dialog occupies the editor.

When ui.select / ui.input / ui.editor / ui.custom mounts a component taller
than the terminal, the "Working..." spinner above it scrolls into native
scrollback but keeps ticking every 80ms. The differential renderer cannot
touch lines that left the viewport, so every tick falls through to a full
clear+redraw, which the user sees as constant flicker.

Upstream discussion: https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/pull/3105
Drop once a release contains the Loader.pause() fix.

